{#
  hx-checkbox-group — Drupal Twig Template
  ==========================================

  Server-renders the hx-checkbox-group custom element with its hx-checkbox children.
  The group is form-associated via ElementInternals and manages multi-value form
  submission automatically. The `name` attribute set on the group propagates to all
  child checkboxes — no Drupal behavior or PHP form alter is required.

  Parameters:
    name        (string)  Required for form submission. Form field name shared by all
                          child checkboxes. Drupal Form API field names use bracket notation
                          for array values (e.g., 'allergies[]').
    label       (string)  Required. Legend text displayed above the checkbox group.
    options     (array)   Required. Array of checkbox options. Each item must have:
                            - value (string): submitted form value
                            - label (string): visible checkbox label
                          Optional per-item keys:
                            - checked (bool): pre-checked state from server
                            - disabled (bool): disable individual option
                            - help_text (string): per-option guidance text
    required    (bool)    Optional. At least one checkbox must be checked.
    disabled    (bool)    Optional. Disables all checkboxes in the group.
    error       (string)  Optional. Error message displayed below the group.
    help_text   (string)  Optional. Help text displayed below the group label.
    orientation (string)  Optional. One of: vertical | horizontal. Defaults to 'vertical'.
    attributes  (object)  Optional. Additional HTML attributes spread onto the group element.

  Usage examples:

    Basic checkbox group (Drupal form field):
      {% include 'hx-checkbox-group.twig' with {
        name: 'notifications',
        label: 'Notification Preferences',
        options: [
          { value: 'email', label: 'Email notifications' },
          { value: 'sms', label: 'SMS notifications' },
          { value: 'push', label: 'Push notifications' },
        ],
      } %}

    Pre-selected options (server-side state):
      {% include 'hx-checkbox-group.twig' with {
        name: 'symptoms',
        label: 'Current Symptoms',
        options: [
          { value: 'fever', label: 'Fever', checked: 'fever' in patient_symptoms },
          { value: 'cough', label: 'Cough', checked: 'cough' in patient_symptoms },
          { value: 'fatigue', label: 'Fatigue', checked: 'fatigue' in patient_symptoms },
        ],
      } %}

    Required group with error state (form validation failure):
      {% include 'hx-checkbox-group.twig' with {
        name: 'consent',
        label: 'Patient Consent',
        required: true,
        error: element['#errors'] ? element['#errors']|render,
        options: [
          { value: 'treatment', label: 'I consent to the proposed treatment plan' },
          { value: 'records', label: 'I consent to sharing medical records' },
        ],
      } %}

    Horizontal layout (compact option sets):
      {% include 'hx-checkbox-group.twig' with {
        name: 'days',
        label: 'Available Days',
        orientation: 'horizontal',
        options: [
          { value: 'mon', label: 'Mon' },
          { value: 'tue', label: 'Tue' },
          { value: 'wed', label: 'Wed' },
          { value: 'thu', label: 'Thu' },
          { value: 'fri', label: 'Fri' },
        ],
      } %}

    Drupal Form API integration (via preprocess hook):
      In your preprocess_form_element hook, map Drupal's `#options` to the `options`
      array and pass `element['#value']` as the checked items list. Example:
        function mytheme_preprocess_checkboxes(&$variables) {
          $element = $variables['element'];
          $variables['options'] = [];
          foreach ($element['#options'] as $value => $label) {
            $variables['options'][] = [
              'value' => $value,
              'label' => $label,
              'checked' => in_array($value, (array) $element['#value']),
            ];
          }
          $variables['name'] = $element['#name'];
          $variables['label'] = $element['#title'];
        }

  Drupal behavior for change events:
    The component dispatches an `hx-change` CustomEvent (bubbles, composed) with
    detail `{ values: string[] }` — the current array of all checked values.
    For standard form submission, no behavior is needed.
    For AJAX-driven patterns:

      (function (Drupal, once) {
        Drupal.behaviors.helixCheckboxGroup = {
          attach: function (context) {
            once('hx-checkbox-group', 'hx-checkbox-group[data-ajax]', context).forEach((grp) => {
              grp.addEventListener('hx-change', (e) => {
                // e.detail.values — array of currently checked values
                Drupal.ajax({ url: grp.dataset.ajax }).execute();
              });
            });
          },
        };
      })(Drupal, once);
#}

<hx-checkbox-group
  {% if name %}name="{{ name }}"{% endif %}
  {% if label %}label="{{ label }}"{% endif %}
  {% if required %}required{% endif %}
  {% if disabled %}disabled{% endif %}
  {% if error %}error="{{ error }}"{% endif %}
  {% if orientation %}orientation="{{ orientation }}"{% endif %}
  {% for key, val in attributes|default({}) %}{{ key }}="{{ val }}" {% endfor %}
>
  {% if help_text %}
    <span slot="help">{{ help_text }}</span>
  {% endif %}

  {% for option in options %}
    <hx-checkbox
      value="{{ option.value }}"
      label="{{ option.label }}"
      {% if option.checked %}checked{% endif %}
      {% if option.disabled %}disabled{% endif %}
      {% if option.help_text %}help-text="{{ option.help_text }}"{% endif %}
    ></hx-checkbox>
  {% endfor %}
</hx-checkbox-group>
